  "excerpt": "<p>Connect your Snowflake Meta-data to DataTools Pro To connect DataTools Pro to your Snowflake account, you will need to use Oauth tokens. Please view our Snowflake setup documentation for detailed steps. In this tutorial we, assume you have completed this step and have the correct tokens and access available. Navigate your Snowflake Databases and Schemas [&hellip;]</p>",
  "content_html": "\n<p></p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-genesis-blocks-gb-columns gb-layout-columns-2 gb-2-col-equal\"><div class=\"gb-layout-column-wrap gb-block-layout-column-gap-2 gb-is-responsive-column\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-genesis-blocks-gb-column gb-block-layout-column\"><div class=\"gb-block-layout-column-inner\">\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img data-dominant-color=\"9fbbcd\" data-has-transparency=\"true\" style=\"--dominant-color: #9fbbcd;\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"1024\" src=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/SNowflake-to-Salesforce-1024x1024.webp\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-11071 has-transparency\" srcset=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/SNowflake-to-Salesforce-1024x1024.webp 1024w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/SNowflake-to-Salesforce-300x300.webp 300w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/SNowflake-to-Salesforce-150x150.webp 150w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/SNowflake-to-Salesforce-768x768.webp 768w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/SNowflake-to-Salesforce-600x600.webp 600w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/SNowflake-to-Salesforce-400x400.webp 400w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/SNowflake-to-Salesforce-45x45.webp 45w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/SNowflake-to-Salesforce-png.webp 1080w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<div id=\"ez-toc-container\" class=\"ez-toc-v2_0_76 counter-hierarchy ez-toc-counter ez-toc-grey ez-toc-container-direction\">\n<div class=\"ez-toc-title-container\">\n<p class=\"ez-toc-title\" style=\"cursor:inherit\">Table of Contents</p>\n<span class=\"ez-toc-title-toggle\"><a href=\"#\" class=\"ez-toc-pull-right ez-toc-btn ez-toc-btn-xs ez-toc-btn-default ez-toc-toggle\" aria-label=\"Toggle Table of Content\"><span class=\"ez-toc-js-icon-con\"><span class=\"\"><span class=\"eztoc-hide\" style=\"display:none;\">Toggle</span><span class=\"ez-toc-icon-toggle-span\"><svg style=\"fill: #999;color:#999\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" class=\"list-377408\" width=\"20px\" height=\"20px\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\"><path d=\"M6 6H4v2h2V6zm14 0H8v2h12V6zM4 11h2v2H4v-2zm16 0H8v2h12v-2zM4 16h2v2H4v-2zm16 0H8v2h12v-2z\" fill=\"currentColor\"></path></svg><svg style=\"fill: #999;color:#999\" class=\"arrow-unsorted-368013\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"10px\" height=\"10px\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" version=\"1.2\" baseProfile=\"tiny\"><path d=\"M18.2 9.3l-6.2-6.3-6.2 6.3c-.2.2-.3.4-.3.7s.1.5.3.7c.2.2.4.3.7.3h11c.3 0 .5-.1.7-.3.2-.2.3-.5.3-.7s-.1-.5-.3-.7zM5.8 14.7l6.2 6.3 6.2-6.3c.2-.2.3-.5.3-.7s-.1-.5-.3-.7c-.2-.2-.4-.3-.7-.3h-11c-.3 0-.5.1-.7.3-.2.2-.3.5-.3.7s.1.5.3.7z\"/></svg></span></span></span></a></span></div>\n<nav><ul class='ez-toc-list ez-toc-list-level-1 ' ><ul class='ez-toc-list-level-4' ><li class='ez-toc-heading-level-4'><ul class='ez-toc-list-level-4' ><li class='ez-toc-heading-level-4'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-1\" href=\"https://datatoolspro.com/tutorials/data-mapping-snowflake-to-salesforce/#Related_Links\" >Related Links</a></li></ul></li></ul></li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-2\" href=\"https://datatoolspro.com/tutorials/data-mapping-snowflake-to-salesforce/#Data_Mapping_Snowflake_to_Salesforce_with_DataTools_Pro\" >Data Mapping Snowflake to Salesforce with DataTools Pro</a></li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-3\" href=\"https://datatoolspro.com/tutorials/data-mapping-snowflake-to-salesforce/#Connect_your_Snowflake_Meta-data_to_DataTools_Pro\" >Connect your Snowflake Meta-data to DataTools Pro</a></li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-4\" href=\"https://datatoolspro.com/tutorials/data-mapping-snowflake-to-salesforce/#Navigate_your_Snowflake_Databases_and_Schemas\" >Navigate your Snowflake Databases and Schemas</a></li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-5\" href=\"https://datatoolspro.com/tutorials/data-mapping-snowflake-to-salesforce/#Data_Mapping_Snowflake_to_Salesforce\" >Data Mapping Snowflake to Salesforce</a></li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-6\" href=\"https://datatoolspro.com/tutorials/data-mapping-snowflake-to-salesforce/#Additional_Tutorials_Data_Mapping_Migration\" >Additional Tutorials: Data Mapping &amp; Migration</a></li></ul></nav></div>\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading has-medium-font-size\"><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Related_Links\"></span>Related Links<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"></span></h4>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://datatoolspro.com/tutorials/how-to-generate-snowflake-client-id-and-secret-for-oauth/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" title=\"Setup SNowflake\">Configure Snowflake for metadata sharing with DataTools Pro</a></p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://datatoolspro.com/tutorials/data-migration-scorecard-for-salesforce/\" title=\"Data Migration Scorecard for Salesforce\">DataTools migration and data mapping features</a></p>\n\n\n\n<p></p>\n</div></div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-genesis-blocks-gb-column gb-block-layout-column\"><div class=\"gb-block-layout-column-inner\">\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Data_Mapping_Snowflake_to_Salesforce_with_DataTools_Pro\"></span>Data Mapping Snowflake to Salesforce with DataTools Pro<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"></span></h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Data mapping Snowflake to Salesforce objects is often referred to as reverse ETL. The concept is data warehouse and analytical processes produce data that is valuable to your customer relationship management. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you are using Snowflake to facilitate a <a href=\"https://datatoolspro.com/salesforce-migration-app/\" title=\"New 2024 Salesforce data migration tool\">data migration </a>or performing regular data movement from Snowflake to Salesforce, keeping track of mapping should follow a rigid process.</p>\n</div></div>\n</div></div>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Connect_your_Snowflake_Meta-data_to_DataTools_Pro\"></span>Connect your Snowflake Meta-data to DataTools Pro<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"></span></h2>\n\n\n\n<p>To connect DataTools Pro to your Snowflake account, you will need to use Oauth tokens. Please view our <a href=\"https://datatoolspro.com/tutorials/how-to-generate-snowflake-client-id-and-secret-for-oauth/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" title=\"Snowflake setup for DataTools Pro\">Snowflake setup documentation</a> for detailed steps. In this tutorial we, assume you have completed this step and have the correct tokens and access available. </p>\n\n\n\n<ol class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><a href=\"https://datatoolspro.com/tutorials/how-to-generate-snowflake-client-id-and-secret-for-oauth/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" title=\"Setup SNowflake\">Acquire your Snowflake account and generate Oath tokens</a></li>\n\n\n\n<li>Login to <a href=\"https://app.datatoolspro.com\" title=\"\">DataTools Pro</a></li>\n\n\n\n<li>Go to Settings</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Click Snowflake integration</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Enter your Account and Oath credentials.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Click Connect</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Grant access from your Oauth credentials to your Snowflake instane</li>\n</ol>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large is-resized\"><img data-dominant-color=\"f0f3f6\" data-has-transparency=\"false\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"961\" src=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/image-6-1024x961.webp\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-11075 not-transparent\" style=\"--dominant-color: #f0f3f6; width:340px;height:auto\" srcset=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/image-6-1024x961.webp 1024w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/image-6-300x281.webp 300w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/image-6-768x721.webp 768w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/image-6-png.webp 1116w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Navigate_your_Snowflake_Databases_and_Schemas\"></span>Navigate your Snowflake Databases and Schemas<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"></span></h2>\n\n\n\n<p>From the Snowflake settings screen in DataTools Pro</p>\n\n\n\n<ol class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Click on the &#8220;Databases&#8221; icon</li>\n</ol>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large is-resized\"><img data-dominant-color=\"f8f8f8\" data-has-transparency=\"false\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"240\" src=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/image-7-1024x240.webp\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-11076 not-transparent\" style=\"--dominant-color: #f8f8f8; width:441px;height:auto\" srcset=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/image-7-1024x240.webp 1024w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/image-7-300x70.webp 300w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/image-7-768x180.webp 768w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/image-7-png.webp 1075w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>2. Select the Schema you would like to view</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img data-dominant-color=\"f9fafa\" data-has-transparency=\"false\" style=\"--dominant-color: #f9fafa;\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"465\" src=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/image-8-1024x465.webp\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-11077 not-transparent\" srcset=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/image-8-1024x465.webp 1024w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/image-8-300x136.webp 300w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/image-8-768x349.webp 768w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/image-8-1536x698.webp 1536w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/image-8-2048x930.webp 2048w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>3. Select the Table within the schema</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img data-dominant-color=\"fafafa\" data-has-transparency=\"false\" style=\"--dominant-color: #fafafa;\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"348\" src=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/image-9-1024x348.webp\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-11078 not-transparent\" srcset=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/image-9-1024x348.webp 1024w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/image-9-300x102.webp 300w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/image-9-768x261.webp 768w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/image-9-1536x522.webp 1536w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/image-9-2048x696.webp 2048w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>4. Drill into the Table to view fields</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img data-dominant-color=\"f9f9f9\" data-has-transparency=\"false\" style=\"--dominant-color: #f9f9f9;\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"378\" src=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/image-10-1024x378.webp\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-11079 not-transparent\" srcset=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/image-10-1024x378.webp 1024w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/image-10-300x111.webp 300w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/image-10-768x283.webp 768w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/image-10-1536x567.webp 1536w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/image-10-2048x756.webp 2048w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Data_Mapping_Snowflake_to_Salesforce\"></span>Data Mapping Snowflake to Salesforce<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"></span></h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Our team built DataTools Pro after spending hundreds of hours mapping data migrations, ETL, and reverse ETP jobs in Excel. Learn how to configure your own Salesforce data mapping tool which can also help you document your <a href=\"https://datatoolspro.com/tutorials/salesforce-field-dictionary-with-datatools-pro/\" title=\"Create Salesforce Field Dictionary with DataTools Pro\">data dictionary</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>From within the DataTools Pro migration tab</p>\n\n\n\n<p>1. Select Snowflake Source Data</p>\n\n\n\n<p>2. Click the &#8220;Get from Snowflake&#8221; link</p>\n\n\n\n<ol class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li></li>\n</ol>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img data-dominant-color=\"a8aaaa\" data-has-transparency=\"false\" style=\"--dominant-color: #a8aaaa;\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"455\" src=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/image-11-1024x455.webp\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-11080 not-transparent\" srcset=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/image-11-1024x455.webp 1024w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/image-11-300x133.webp 300w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/image-11-768x341.webp 768w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/image-11-1536x683.webp 1536w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/image-11-2048x910.webp 2048w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>3. Select the saved <a href=\"https://datatoolspro.com/tutorials/how-to-generate-snowflake-client-id-and-secret-for-oauth/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" title=\"Configure Snowflake in DataTools Pro\">Snowflake instance configured in DataTools Pro settings</a></p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large is-resized\"><img data-dominant-color=\"f5f8f7\" data-has-transparency=\"false\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"717\" height=\"1024\" src=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/image-12-717x1024.webp\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-11081 not-transparent\" style=\"--dominant-color: #f5f8f7; width:306px;height:auto\" srcset=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/image-12-717x1024.webp 717w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/image-12-210x300.webp 210w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/image-12-768x1097.webp 768w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/image-12-png.webp 860w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 717px) 100vw, 717px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>4. Set the global migrate status for this object so as you map fields DataTools Pro can automatically set a status for the field you map from Snowflake to Salesforce. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>DataTools Pro will import the schema from Snowflake and give you an opportuinty to quickly fine tune.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>5. Auto-match fields to Salesforce when the name is the same (case insensitive process).</p>\n\n\n\n<p>6. Click Save</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large is-resized\"><img data-dominant-color=\"eaf1ef\" data-has-transparency=\"false\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"610\" height=\"1024\" src=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/image-13-610x1024.webp\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-11082 not-transparent\" style=\"--dominant-color: #eaf1ef; width:323px;height:auto\" srcset=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/image-13-610x1024.webp 610w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/image-13-179x300.webp 179w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/image-13-768x1289.webp 768w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/image-13-png.webp 870w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 610px) 100vw, 610px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Additional_Tutorials_Data_Mapping_Migration\"></span>Additional Tutorials: Data Mapping &amp; Migration<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"></span></h2>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-genesis-blocks-gb-columns gb-layout-columns-3 gb-3-col-equal\"><div class=\"gb-layout-column-wrap gb-block-layout-column-gap-2 gb-is-responsive-column\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-genesis-blocks-gb-column gb-block-layout-column\"><div class=\"gb-block-layout-column-inner\">\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed is-type-wp-embed is-provider-datatools-pro wp-block-embed-datatools-pro\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\n<div class=\"ratio ratio-16x9\"><blockquote class=\"wp-embedded-content\" data-secret=\"X7hu1XI90K\"><a href=\"https://datatoolspro.com/tutorials/salesforce-migration-field-mapping-details/\">Salesforce Migration Field Mapping Details</a></blockquote><iframe loading=\"lazy\" class=\"wp-embedded-content\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts\" security=\"restricted\" style=\"position: absolute; visibility: hidden;\" title=\"&#8220;Salesforce Migration Field Mapping Details&#8221; &#8212; DataTools Pro\" src=\"https://datatoolspro.com/tutorials/salesforce-migration-field-mapping-details/embed/#?secret=xSx2nXH0mu#?secret=X7hu1XI90K\" data-secret=\"X7hu1XI90K\" width=\"600\" height=\"338\" frameborder=\"0\" marginwidth=\"0\" marginheight=\"0\" scrolling=\"no\"></iframe></div>\n</div></figure>\n</div></div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-genesis-blocks-gb-column gb-block-layout-column\"><div class=\"gb-block-layout-column-inner\">\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed is-type-wp-embed is-provider-datatools-pro wp-block-embed-datatools-pro\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\n<div class=\"ratio ratio-16x9\"><blockquote class=\"wp-embedded-content\" data-secret=\"agCLcqV6UU\"><a href=\"https://datatoolspro.com/tutorials/mapping-and-migrating-salesforce-picklists/\">Mapping and Migrating Salesforce Picklists</a></blockquote><iframe loading=\"lazy\" class=\"wp-embedded-content\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts\" security=\"restricted\" style=\"position: absolute; visibility: hidden;\" title=\"&#8220;Mapping and Migrating Salesforce Picklists&#8221; &#8212; DataTools Pro\" src=\"https://datatoolspro.com/tutorials/mapping-and-migrating-salesforce-picklists/embed/#?secret=iEfHzHtdLi#?secret=agCLcqV6UU\" data-secret=\"agCLcqV6UU\" width=\"600\" height=\"338\" frameborder=\"0\" marginwidth=\"0\" marginheight=\"0\" scrolling=\"no\"></iframe></div>\n</div></figure>\n</div></div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-genesis-blocks-gb-column gb-block-layout-column\"><div class=\"gb-block-layout-column-inner\">\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed is-type-wp-embed is-provider-datatools-pro wp-block-embed-datatools-pro\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\n<div class=\"ratio ratio-16x9\"><blockquote class=\"wp-embedded-content\" data-secret=\"Vk4KFzgUmF\"><a href=\"https://datatoolspro.com/tutorials/migration-export-sql/\">Migration Export SQL</a></blockquote><iframe loading=\"lazy\" class=\"wp-embedded-content\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts\" security=\"restricted\" style=\"position: absolute; visibility: hidden;\" title=\"&#8220;Migration Export SQL&#8221; &#8212; DataTools Pro\" src=\"https://datatoolspro.com/tutorials/migration-export-sql/embed/#?secret=EmD95Xcnwo#?secret=Vk4KFzgUmF\" data-secret=\"Vk4KFzgUmF\" width=\"600\" height=\"338\" frameborder=\"0\" marginwidth=\"0\" marginheight=\"0\" scrolling=\"no\"></iframe></div>\n</div></figure>\n</div></div>\n</div></div>\n\n\n\n<p>Your meta data is now imported to use with <a href=\"https://datatoolspro.com/tutorials/data-migration-scorecard-for-salesforce/\" title=\"Data Migration Scorecard for Salesforce\">DataTools migration and data mapping features</a></p>\n"
}